Type: Package
Package: pcurveMix
Title: Computations and Fitting for a P-Curve Mixture Model
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rolf", "Ulrich", , "ulrich@uni-tuebingen.de", role = "aut"),
    person("Jeff", "Miller", , "miller@psy.otago.ac.nz", role = "cre")
  )
Description: Package for computations and fitting with the p-curve mixture
    model of Ulrich & Miller (2026).  According to the model, p values
    from statistical tests come from a mixture distribution with some
    proportion \pi of studies having a true effect (H1 is true), whereas
    the remaining studies have no true effect (H0 is true).  Among studies
    with H1 true, the noncentrality parameter is normally distributed with
    mean \mu and standard deviation \sigma.  Packages routines provide the
    PDF and CDF values of specific p's given particular values of \pi,
    \mu, and \sigma, and they estimate the underlying \pi, \mu, and \sigma
    values from a set of observed p values.
